item.title: Error!
item.dc:creator: @Kalphiter Kalphiter
item.description:
@Kalphiter wrote:

I know your problem

You might see a command like

[code]} else if(command.equalsIgnoreCase(“commandname”){

some stuffs[/code]

Than a new command

Notice how “} else if” starts with a bracket.

That bracket ends the last command. It’s thinking that customcommand void is finished and now it’s a new void. (usually public void fromBank is after the commands). So get rid of that curly bracket in the beginning.
